You can apply your own window style.<br />
<ul>
<li>Download the Source Code</li>
<li>copy file FirstFloor.ModernUI --&gt; Themes --&gt;ModernWindow.xaml to your own project to the Themes folder</li>
<li>Customize the modern window</li>
<li>Connect this resource to your window</li>
</ul>
<pre><code>    &lt;Window.Resources&gt;
        &lt;ResourceDictionary&gt;
            &lt;ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries&gt;
                &lt;ResourceDictionary Source=&quot;Themes/ModernWindow.xaml&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;/ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries&gt;
        &lt;/ResourceDictionary&gt;
    &lt;/Window.Resources&gt;</code></pre>

<ul>
<li>Create a resource key  </li>
</ul>
<pre><code>&lt;Style TargetType=&quot;controls:ModernWindow&quot; x:Key=&quot;CustomWindow&quot;&gt;</code></pre>

<ul>
<li>and apply the custom style to your window</li>
</ul>
<pre><code>    &lt;Window.Style&gt;
        &lt;StaticResource ResourceKey=&quot;CustomWindow&quot;&gt;&lt;/StaticResource&gt;
    &lt;/Window.Style&gt;</code></pre>
